  "texts": [
    "We also demonstrate single-qubit Clifford gate fidelities up to 99.85% and a two-qubit gate fidelity of 98.92%.",
    "These advances overcome the fundamental limitation that the thermal energy must be well below the qubit energies for the high-fidelity operation to be possible, surmounting a main obstacle in the pathway to scalable and fault-tolerant quantum computation.",
    "To realize the promised benefits of quantum computing, large arrays of qubits will need to operate within densely packed cryogenic platforms, and the heating effects will eventually impose temperatures well above the millikelvin regime 12, [14] [15] [16] [17] [18].",
    "Spins in semiconductor quantum dots are rising candidates for this undertaking, thanks to their low error rates, long information hold time and industrial manufacturing compatibility 2, 3, 6, 22.",
    "Initial studies of spin qubit operation above 1 K have verified its feasibility, despite suffering from degraded state-preparation-and-measurement (SPAM) and gate fidelities [15] [16] [17] [18]."
